description.text:
Mine was printed at 30mm/sec, .2mm layer height, 20% infill (for the base), 2 vertical shells (slic3r seems to understand that the bowl should be only one shell thick), 1.75mm PLA. These are nicer when printed with a slightly translucent PLA.
I recommend printing at least four glasses at the same time. Any less and they will not have a chance to cool down. If you see your print start to fail (stem breaks or base unsticks) you can let it run and get some neat &quot;art.&quot;
Drink responsibly!
